Description: Fully functioning and playing properly. Includes original manual and two wrenches. Stand in the pictures is not included. I originally purchased this guitar as a factory second due to the dings and minor crack by the knob in the pictures. All is cosmetic. This guitar is fully functioning and playing properly. There is an S stamped on the back of the headstock. The RGAT62 is a hardtail 6-string electric built around a Mahogany body wing body. Its contoured top not only looks sleek—it creates a softer, more comfortable edge where the player's right forearm rests. The Wizard III 5pc Maple/ Walnut through constructed neck feature jumbo frets and a jatoba fretboard that not only provides optimal articulation, but enhances playing speed as well. This neck and fretboard combination provides a smooth, inviting playing surface and contributes to the RGAT62's warm, well-defined tonality. DiMarzio Air Norton and The Tone Zone pickups were chosen for the inspiring way they complement each other to create a wide pallet of tonal options that add fire and improve sustain, yet retain clarity. Wired through a 5-way selector switch, they can be combined in a variety of configurations that offer numerous tonal options. A simple, yet solid fixed bridge provides stable, dependable tuning and accurate intonation. Features:- Mahogany body wing body - Wizard III 5pc Maple/ Walnut through constructed neck - DiMarzio Air Norton and The Tone Zone pickups - Fixed bridge for stable, dependable tuning and accurate intonation Specs: - Neck: Wizard III 5pc Maple/Walnut neck-through - Top: Contoured top - Body: Mahogany wing - Fretboard: Jatoba - Dot Inlay: Off-set white dot inlay - Frets: Jumbo - Neck pickup: DiMarzio Air Norton (H) - Bridge pickup: DiMarzio Tone Zone (H) - Switch: 5-way selector switch - Bridge: Fixed bridge - Hardware: Black
